name: packing, fibre cement product | packing, fibre cement product | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/696/documentation

The production amount used for normalization is 20'000t/a. This module is assumed to be valid also for plants up to 100'000t/a. The lifespan of the infrastructure and the land occupation are assumed to be 50 years.;[This dataset was already contained in the ecoinvent database version 2. It was not individually updated during the transfer to ecoinvent version 3. Life Cycle Impact Assessment results may still have changed, as they are affected by changes in the supply chain, i.e. in other datasets. This dataset was generated following the ecoinvent quality guidelines for version 2. It may have been subject to central changes described in the ecoinvent version 3 change report (http://www.ecoinvent.org/database/ecoinvent-version-3/reports-of-changes/), and the results of the central updates were reviewed extensively. The changes added e.g. consistent water flows and other information throughout the database. The documentation of this dataset can be found in the ecoinvent reports of version 2, which are still available via the ecoinvent website. The change report linked above covers all central changes that were made during the conversion process.]



Includes the process of packing, transportation, and loading of the bags on paletts. The machines, the waste treatment after use by the end-user of the fibre cement products and the transports of the packing materials are included.
category: N:Administrative and support service activities/82:Office administrative, office support and other business support activities/829:Business support service activities n.e.c./8292:Packaging activities

processDocumentation.geographyDescription: Data from a company producing lime products in Switzerland are adjusted
processDocumentation.technologyDescription: Assumed that packaging is the same as for lime products
processDocumentation.dataTreatmentDescription: See geography This dataset has been copied from an original dataset covering the geography CH. The uncertainty has been adjusted accordingly.
